Episode 1
Timid teacher Ian Telford joins the stag weekend of his brother-in-law Johnners and several of his obnoxious friends, as they embark on a deer-stalking adventure in the remote Scottish Highlands, organised by best man Ledge. But it's not long before the hunters become the prey, and their friendship is tested to the limit in a ruthless battle for survival.

Episode 2
The stag weekend from hell continues as the ever-diminishing group of friends are joined by a suspicious latecomer, who divides loyalties and leads them deeper into danger.
Trapped in the home of their seeming assassin, the stag party are divided over their next move. But a resourceful gatecrasher arrives and offers to lead them to apparent safety, only to divide them further and cause more secrets and blood to be spilled.

Episode 3
The remaining members of the group pull together in an attempt to uncover the identity of their killer and survive the stag weekend from hell.
Ever closer to learning the identity of the killer, the four remaining members of the stag party realise they must make a final stand if they are to survive. But will the killer, and their past, catch up with them before they can figure it all out? And will Ian fulfil his promise to his sister and keep Johnners from a grizzly end?
